******
[1] Global - GPEI/WHO WPV1 (ES Pakistan), cVDPV2 (AFP Afghanistan, DR Congo, Nigeria, Tajikistan), cVDPV1 (ES Madagascar)
Date: 5 Aug 2021
Source: Global Polio Eradication Initiative / WHO [edited]
https://polioeradication.org/polio-today/polio-now/this-week/


Poliovirus Weekly Update as of 4-Aug-2021, World Health Organization
----------------------------------------
New wild poliovirus isolates reported this week:
Acute flaccid paralysis [AFP] cases: 0
Environmental samples [ES]: 1
Others: 0

New cVDPV isolates reported this week:
AFP cases: 25
ES: 13
Others: 4

Summary of new wild poliovirus [WPV] and circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus [cVDPV] this week (AFP cases and ES positives):
- Pakistan: 1 WPV1 positive ES
- Afghanistan: 1 cVDPV2 case
- DR Congo: 1 cVDPV2 case
- Madagascar: 7 cVDPV1 positive ES
- Nigeria: 16 cVDPV2 cases and 6 cVDPV2 positive ES
- Tajikistan: 7 cVDPV2 cases

Afghanistan
- No wild poliovirus type 1 (WPV1) case was reported this week. There is 1 case reported in 2021 while the total number of 2020 cases remains at 56.
- 1 case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported in Wardak bringing the number of 2021 cases to 43. There were 308 cVDPV2 cases reported in 2020.

Pakistan
- No wild poliovirus type 1 (WPV1) case was reported this week. There is 1 case reported in 2021. The total number of 2020 cases remains at 84.
- 1 WPV1 positive environmental sample was reported in Sindh.
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. The number of 2021 cases remains at 8. There were 135 cases reported in 2020.

Angola
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There were 3 cVDPV2 cases reported in 2020.

Benin
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 2 cases reported in 2021 so far. There were 3 cVDPV2 cases reported in 2020. These cases are all linked to the Jigawa outbreak in Nigeria.

Burkina Faso
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There is 1 case reported in 2021 so far. The number of 2020 cases remains at 65. The country is affected by different outbreaks, 1 linked to the Jigawa outbreak in Nigeria and 1 to the Savanes outbreak in Togo.

Cameroon
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There were 7 cVDPV2 cases reported in 2020.

Central African Republic
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There were 4 cVDPV2 cases reported in 2020.

Chad
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There were 99 cVDPV2 cases reported in 2020 from 3 different outbreaks.
- The risk of further cVDPV2 spread across the Lake Chad subregion remains high.

Congo
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 2 cases reported in 2021. There were 2 cases reported in 2020.

Cote d'Ivoire
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. The number of 2020 cases remains at 61.

Democratic Republic of the Congo (DR Congo)
- 1 case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported in Mongala. There are 10 cases reported in 2021 so far. The total number of 2020 cases remains at 81.

Egypt
- No cVDPV2 positive environmental sample was reported this week. There are 10 positive samples reported in 2021. There was 1 positive sample reported in 2020.

Ethiopia
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 36 cases from 2020 while the number of 2021 cases remains at 6.

Gambia
- No cVDPV2 positive environmental sample was reported this week. 2 positive samples linked to the Jigawa outbreak in Nigeria were reported last week.

Ghana
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There were 12 cases reported in 2020.

Guinea
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 6 cases in 2021. The total number of 2020 cases remains at 44.

Kenya
- No cVDPV2 positive environmental sample was reported this week. There was 1 cVDPV2 positive environmental sample reported in 2020 and 1 in 2021. The virus is linked to the Banadir outbreak in Somalia.

Liberia
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 3 cVDPV2 cases in the country.

Madagascar
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 1 (cVDPV1) was reported this week. There are 6 cases in 2021 and 2 from 2020.
- 7 cVDPV1 positive environmental samples were reported: 4 in Boeni and 3 in Anosy.

Malaysia
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 1 (cVDPV1) was reported this week. There was 1 case in 2020.

Mali
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. The number of 2020 cases remains at 48.

Niger
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. The number of 2020 cases remains at 10.

Nigeria
- 16 cases of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) were reported: 3 each in Jigawa and Sokoto, 2 in Kano and 1 each in Borno, Gombe, Oyo, Abia, Zamfara, Imo, Kebbi and Nasarawa. The number of 2021 cases now stands at 65. There were 8 cases reported in 2020.
- 6 cVDPV2 positive environmental samples were reported; 1 each in Jigawa, Bauchi and Plateau, and 3 in Abia.

Senegal
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. The number of 2021 cases remains at 13.

Sierra Leone
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 4 cases in 2021 while the number of 2020 cases remains at 10.

Somalia
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There were 14 cVDPV2 cases reported in 2020.

South Sudan
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 59 cVDPV2 cases in the country; 9 in 2021 and 50 in 2020.

Sudan
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. The number of 2020 cases remains at 58. The initial viruses were linked to the ongoing outbreak in Chad followed by local transmission.

Tajikistan
- 7 cases of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) were reported: 6 in Khatlon and 1 in DRS bringing the number of 2021 cases to 23. There was 1 case reported in 2020.

Togo
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There were 9 cases reported in 2020.

Uganda
- No cVDPV2 positive environmental sample was reported this week. 2 positive samples linked to the N'Djamena outbreak in Chad were reported in Kampala last week.

Yemen
- No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 1 (cVDPV1) was reported this week. There are 3 cases reported in 2021 so far and a total of 35 altogether.


Officially reported WPV1 and cVDPV cases as of 03 August 2021
Wild poliovirus (WPV)
- Total global WPV1 cases in 2021: 2 (compared with 94 for the same period in 2020)
- Total global WPV1 cases in 2020: 140

Circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus (cVDPV) cases
- Total global cVDPV cases in 2021: 204 (compared with 223 for the same period in 2020)
- Total global cVDPV cases in 2020: 1103

--
communicated by:
ProMED
<promed@rpomedmail.org>

[In keeping with the global picture in 2020 and 2021, cVDPVs are causing more AFP cases in numerous countries. Nigeria and Tajikistan seem to be the current "hotspots" but many countries have had transmission during 2021 to date.

As for WPV1 (wild poliovirus type 1), after an interval of 4 weeks with no WPV1 detected in neither AFP cases, environmental samples nor asymptomatic individuals in areas with documented positive environmental samples, this week there is a positive environmental sample for WPV1 in Sindh. Since the beginning of 2021, there have been positive environmental samples for WHO in all 4 major areas in Pakistan (Sindh, Punjab, Khyber Pakhtunkhwa, Balochistan and Punjab).

At the risk of sounding like a broken record, globally, right now, the risk of disease from the vaccine is greater than the risk from the disease from the wild virus.

A map showing the locations of each confirmed case of polio worldwide in the past 12 months can be found at https://polioeradication.org/polio-today/polio-now/. One can see cases of cVDPV in a band across Africa and in Afghanistan and Pakistan, cVDPV1 in Madagascar and Yemen, and WPV1 in Afghanistan and Pakistan.

For a map of Nigeria showing states, see https://nigerianfinder.com/map-of-nigeria-states/. - Mod.MPP]

******
[2] Pakistan: violence against polio worker
[A] Khyber Tribal area
Date: 27 Jul 2021
Source: The News [edited]
https://www.thenews.com.pk/print/874560-polio-worker-attacked-in-landikotal


Unidentified gunmen shot and injured a polio supervisor late on Thursday [5 Aug 2021] night in Ashkhel village of Landikotal tehsil [township] in Khyber tribal district, police said on Friday [6 Aug 2021].

The sources said that [the] polio supervisor in the area and is also the chairman of Landikotal Falahi Tanzeem, was at his hujra [sitting room] with guests when a few gunmen opened indiscriminate fire from outside the compound, aiming at the main gate. According to family sources, the incident took place around 8 pm when his son and another person were present at the hujra's lawn. As a result, [he] was wounded while others remained safe in the incident.

Later, the police reached the site and cordoned off the area to collect evidence.

The polio supervisor was rushed to the District Headquarters Hospital in Landikotal wherefrom he was shifted to Hayatabad Medical Complex in Peshawar. No group or individual had claimed responsibility for the attack when this report was filed.

--
